Explanation for Palindrome program :

Definition :
A string is said to be palindrome only if the word read from left to right is same as the word read from right to left . 

Intuition:

A palindrome reads the same from both left to right and right to left.
Instead of creating a reversed copy of the string, we can compare characters from both ends simultaneously using two pointers algorithm.

The left pointer starts at the beginning of the string.
The right pointer starts at the end of the string.

Since spaces and special characters do not affect whether a string is a palindrome, we skip them.
We also convert uppercase letters to lowercase so that 'A' and 'a' are treated as equal.

If at any point the two valid characters do not match, the string is not a palindrome.If the pointers cross without finding a mismatch, the string is a palindrome.

Code :
First we initialize two pointers left and right . left pointer has value 0 (starting index ) and right pointer has value len(s)-1 (ending index ). We iterate through each characters. 
Whether if s[left] is non alphanumeric character like spaces , commas , full stop or a question marks etc we skip it by changing the pointer one step ahead .
Similarly if s[right] is non alphanumeric character we skip it by saying right-=1
Our main goal is to make both pointers left and right become equal at some point in future which is when the while loop ends

For example :
s='racecar'

r a c e c a r
↑           ↑
L           R
Here first left=0 and right=len(s)-1 and  s[left]='r' and s[right]='r' . s[left]==s[right]  ------>  TRUE✅   we do left+=1 and right-=1

r a c e c a r
  ↑       ↑
  L       R

Next left=1 ad right=len(s)-2 and s[left]='a' and s[right]='a' . s[left==s[right]  -------------->   TRUE✅    we do left+=1 and right-=1

r a c e c a r
    ↑   ↑
    L   R

Next left=2 ad right=len(s)-3 and s[left]='c' and s[right]='c' . s[left==s[right]  -------------->   TRUE✅    we do left+=1 and right-=1

r a c e c a r
      ↑
     L,R

Now left=3 and right=len(s)-4 and both s[left] and s[right] points to same character 'e' . This is the condition when our while loop ends .
Since we got TRUE in all the time when we change the pointers . We can find that the string is a palindrome.

If during this process if there exists any mismatch , we return False and come out of the while loop.

